made 2021

1.75ish pounds "chuck roast"
onion soup mix (https://tastesbetterfromscratch.com/homemade-dry-onion-soup-mix/)
worcestershire sauce, "sprinkle it 'round"
2C water
2 Yukon gold, discs
some shredded carrot
1 large onion

wash meat, rub with soup mix, put in center of dish, spray Worcestershire sauce, add water around it
cover tight with aluminum foil, 50 minutes at 350F
pull out, add vegetable, another 90 minutes at 350F

let meat cool and then freeze briefly before slicing

